LICENSE
=======

This project is multi-licensed **by layer**. Each file is governed by the license
for its layer below. SPDX license identifiers are used throughout; the full,
verbatim license texts are in the `LICENSES/` directory.

LICENSING (three layers) — ADOPTED
----------------------------------

  - Software   (iOS app, firmware)               ->  Apache-2.0        (LICENSES/Apache-2.0.txt)
  - Hardware   (CAD, 3D-print files, schematic)  ->  CERN-OHL-W-2.0    (LICENSES/CERN-OHL-W-2.0.txt)
  - Documentation                                ->  CC-BY-4.0         (LICENSES/CC-BY-4.0.txt)

Copyright (c) 2020-2026 Tomoyuki Shishido and the bFaaaP contributors.

Which layer a file is in:
  - ios-app/** and **/firmware/**                 -> Apache-2.0
  - **/hardware/** (CAD, schematic, 3D-print)     -> CERN-OHL-W-2.0
  - docs/** and documentation (*.md, figures)     -> CC-BY-4.0
  Each subtree's README also states its layer; when in doubt, contact the authors.

Why this split:
  - Apache-2.0 for code gives users an EXPLICIT PATENT GRANT (plus a patent-
    retaliation clause), which matters for a patented project; MIT is silent on
    patents. Apache also keeps trademarks separate (protecting bFaaaP(R)).
  - Hardware and documentation are not software, so they use an open-hardware /
    Creative-Commons license rather than a software license.

PATENTS
-------
The pedal-control method (head-angle threshold + press speed/preference) is
patented in Japan -- JP 6726319 B2 "Auxiliary pedal system" and JP 7004771 B2
"Device controller"; priority-basis PCT (English): WO 2019/176164. Patentees:
Tomoyuki Shishido and Ootaki & Architects (Otaki Architectural Office).

Patent licensing generally depends on the counterparty's intended embodiment,
BUT for genuinely public/open-purpose uses the authors intend to grant a licence
FREE OF CHARGE. In particular, for products or services that help people with
disabilities (and others who need it) participate in society more inclusively --
even commercial, paid ones -- bFaaaP-related patent licensing is, as a matter of
policy, granted FREE OF CHARGE. Contact Tomoyuki Shishido (https://bfaaap.com ;
ORCID 0000-0002-8944-2088).

Scope note: the Apache-2.0 patent grant covers contributions as distributed (the
code). The right to PRACTISE the invention in a physical device is governed by the
separate patent policy above; the NOTICE/README states this so the two are not
confused.

